---
// Hero component for Verum landing page
// Emphasizes engineering substance over marketing pathos
---

<section class="hero-section">
  <div class="hero-content">
    <img src="/verum-logo-512.png" alt="Verum" class="hero-logo" width="120" height="120" />
    <h1 class="hero-title">Verum</h1>
    <p class="hero-tagline">
      Memory safety without runtime cost.<br/>
      Verification without ceremony.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a href="/introduction" class="primary">Get Started</a>
      <a href="/guide/types" class="secondary">Learn the Language</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hero-code">
    <pre class="code-example"><code><span class="comment">// Three-tier references: choose your tradeoff</span>
<span class="keyword">fn</span> <span class="function">process</span>(
    data: <span class="type">&List&lt;Int&gt;</span>,           <span class="comment">// ~15ns CBGR check</span>
    cache: <span class="type">&checked Cache</span>,      <span class="comment">// 0ns, compiler-proven</span>
) <span class="keyword">using</span> [<span class="type">Logger</span>] -> <span class="type">Result&lt;Output, Error&gt;</span> {'{'}
    <span class="comment">// Refinement types catch errors at compile time</span>
    <span class="keyword">let</span> idx: <span class="type">Int where 0 &lt;= self &lt; data.len()</span> = <span class="number">0</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Explicit dependencies via context system</span>
    Logger.info(<span class="string">f"Processing {'{'}data.len(){'}'} items"</span>);

    <span class="keyword">Ok</span>(transform(data, cache))
{'}'}</code></pre>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="features-section">
  <div class="features-grid">
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>⚡ Semantic Types</h3>
      <p>
        <code>List</code>, <code>Text</code>, <code>Map</code> — types describe meaning, not implementation.
        No hidden allocations, no surprise costs.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>🔒 CBGR Memory Safety</h3>
      <p>
        Capability-Based Generational References provide memory safety at ~15ns overhead.
        Promote to <code>&checked</code> for zero-cost when the compiler can prove safety.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>📐 Refinement Types</h3>
      <p>
        <code>Int where 0 <= self</code> — constraints verified at compile time.
        Graduate from runtime checks to static proofs incrementally.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>🔗 Context System</h3>
      <p>
        <code>using [Database, Logger]</code> — explicit dependencies, no hidden state.
        Dependency injection built into the type system.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>✓ Gradual Verification</h3>
      <p>
        Start with dynamic checks, add proofs where they matter.
        SMT-backed verification when you need guarantees.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>⚙️ Cogs Package System</h3>
      <p>
        <code>link math from "vcogs.io/math"</code> — semantic imports.
        Each cog is a gear in your machine.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="tiers-section">
  <h2>Reference Tiers: Your Choice of Tradeoff</h2>
  <div class="tier-comparison">
    <div class="tier-card tier-0">
      <div class="tier-name">&T</div>
      <div class="tier-desc">Full CBGR protection</div>
      <div class="tier-overhead">~15ns per access</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tier-card tier-1">
      <div class="tier-name">&checked T</div>
      <div class="tier-desc">Compiler-proven safe</div>
      <div class="tier-overhead">0ns overhead</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tier-card tier-2">
      <div class="tier-name">&unsafe T</div>
      <div class="tier-desc">Manual safety proof</div>
      <div class="tier-overhead">0ns overhead</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .hero-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    min-height: 70vh;
  }

  .hero-logo {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 20px rgba(67, 97, 238, 0.3));
  }

  .hero-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .hero-code {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero-section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      text-align: center;
      min-height: auto;
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    .hero-code {
      order: 2;
    }
  }
</style>
